vintage.name: Vintage Navajo Concho Shadowbox Sterling Silver Bear ClawBelt Necklace
vintage.description: Navajo Concho Shadowbox Linked Sterling Silver Coral Bear Claw Belt Or Necklace Signed TN  for Thomas Nez.  Has oval cut cabochons.  I used to have a southwest retail store in the 1980's that focused on only Native American jewelry, rugs and pottery. I closed this store in 1995. I personally went to New Mexico to work with the Native American Indians, Navajo and Zuni to buy for my shop. So this belt necklace is vintage but new.From Navajo silversmith Thomas Nez, this is a versatile jewelry accessory with a great design that will get noticed! The piece consists of 22 sterling silver bear paw shadow box links. In the center of each shadowbox is a saw tooth bezel set oval coral cabochon. The top of the links are polished shiny, the inside of the shadowbox has an oxidized finish. The links measure 1 1/8” long by 3/4” high. The length is adjustable up to 37”, allowing the piece to be worn as a longer necklace or a belt. The closure is a hook and eye. The back of one of the links is marked STERLING TN.  Please note that if worn as a belt, it is suggested that it is worn for decoration purposes only as the links are not big or heavy. To dress up your favorite plain sweater or to accessorize your blue jeans, either way you wear it, it looks great! This  belt is quintessential of the Southwest Style. Features a hand tooled Bear Paw pattern with a center coral stone increasing this belt's versatility and value. Remember with shadow boxing design there are two layers of sterling silver on EACH concho making it more valuable.If interested call or text Rebecca at  .  I live in a smoke and pet free environment.  CASH ONLY

fast.name: 2004 Mazda 6 Sport - Fast & Reliable
fast.description: Unfortunately it is time to pass on my absolutely amazing 2004 Mazda 6 Sport Hatchback! It is in great condition, serviced frequently and well taken care of by our local and trusted mechanic at Advanced Auto in Santa Cruz. Runs perfectly, drove it to Yosemite last week and Anaheim about a month ago with absolutely no problems. Just passed Smog. Great gas mileage and a comfortable ride for road trips. Always received premium gas and oil changes every 3,000 miles.Completely upgraded the sound system with a 12inch kicker subwoofer and new speakers and amp (Sounds Incredible). I also put in a touchscreen Pioneer center display that is bluetooth capable and has a usb hookup for your phone to charge and play music. I also installed a back-up camera! This car has really been well taken care of and I am sad to see it go but I am in need of something a bit bigger. There are some signs of age as you can see in the seats and body and the text in the center screen is starting to fade a bit (See Photos). But these minor cosmetic blemishes are truly only aesthetic and do not take away from how amazing this car drives. There are no mechanical issues at all, sometimes a bit of oil does burn off the engine resulting in a smell but we have confirmed with our mechanic that there is no underlying issue associated with this. It’s fast and reliable and will get you where you need to go in comfort and style.The price is $5250 Obo and please feel free to reach out with ANY questions or to schedule a test drive!

famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most sold-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Nice, low action and great intonation. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail. One-of-a-kind cloth gig bag included. Reasonable offers are welcome.

famous.name: 3/4 size Violin - Scott Cao STV850
famous.description: Our child has gone to full size violin, time to sell the beloved 3/4 size. Price includes a sweet sounding violin, well cared for and treated with love. See this YouTube review of this model:  https://youtu.be/Jz9syJBj3YQor this one:https://youtu.be/HrK9-04SdQUPrice includes excellent bow and a great 3/4 sized case, also in excellent condition, and a shoulder rest. This was selected after trying out many violins over a long time, and has really opened up with being played regularly.Great value!You and your child will love the sound this violin can make. If this ad is still posted, the violin is still for sale. We are open to all reasonable offers!Here is an excerpt of a review of this particular model of Scott Cao violin:Another well-crafted series of violins that are considered among the best around. The quality of the Scott Cao 850 violin craftsmanship is unique, and the sound instantly recognizable.Ideally, they are for advanced learners or adults who want to have a great instrument.The violins are replicas of some of the most renowned King Joseph, Lord Wilton, and Ysabel instruments, and all are made in China.Since original violins can cost a small fortune, master luthiers from Scott Cao’s workshop recreate and customize them for advanced and famous violinists.OverviewWhat makes the Scott Cao 850 model a premium instrument is first-grade materials. With Italian spruce and some of the best Bosnian maple on the market, the violins are a rare combination of high-quality wood.All the fittings alongside boxwood are made from Indian ebony, making it one of the most expensive violins.The famous “Strings” magazine states that these violins are among the best performance violins due to their varnish and superiority over similarly priced instruments.FeaturesEvery model is constructed from the finest materials. From the combination of fine maple and spruce, all the way to the best hand-applied varnish that combines special oils to achieve warm and intricate sound qualities.The wood was carefully drained and combined to get the best look and perfect fire lines. With Indian ebony and a whole array of accessories, everything enhances the instrument’s overall durability and beauty.The 850 violins are often called some of the best sounding violins in their price range, and when compared with similar violins, their sound is far superior.What We Like:Premium accessoriesThe fines woodSuperior sound and projectionGreat final changesStructural warrantyFrom this website: https://newviolinist.com/best-scott-cao-violin/

famous.name: Klon Centaur Professional Overdrive (Horsie)
famous.description: At Keith Holland Guitars in Los Gatos, CA, we painstakingly vet both our new and used instruments to make sure we only present instruments of the highest quality.  All of our instruments, old and new, are set up in our world-class repair shop before we display them in our showroom or advertise them online. When you buy from Keith Holland Guitars, you can rest assured that you're in good hands and that your instrument will be ready to play out of the box.Finnegan's Wake:Ever since Bill Finnegan created the Klon in the early 90's, pedal makers have been scrambling to replicate the magical clear transparent overdrive effect made famous by the pedal. Often imitated and rarely equaled, the Klon remains one of the most talked about pedals of all time. A shroud of mystery continually to surrounds the infamous overdrive. Many strong words have been exchanged between pedal builders, armchair scholars and professional musicians, who spend countless hours a discussing (or debating) just what particular component makes the pedal so good. The black goop, an epoxy resin that obscures the pedal's circuit, only adds to the mystery.All hype aside, its really a great sounding pedal. Its simple, easy to use and extremely versatile. It can act as a simple clean boost or used to get more dirt into your sound. It is a worthwhile investment for someone with a great sounding amp who would like to push it into overdrive territory without losing the natural tone of the amp and guitar. This specific Klon has the Horsie decal and a really low serial # at 492This particular pedal is in Good Condition. There is some scratching and wear to the front and sides of the enclosure and substantial scratching to the bottom. It has been lovingly used and studied by its two principal owners and has been in and around our store's possession ever since Keith was a dealer back in the day.
